HEADWORD: Sluggardy
<hw>Slug"gard*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sloggardye</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being a sluggard;
sluggishness; sloth.</def> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Idleness is rotten <qex>sluggardy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slugger</ent>⟦br⟧
